$PAR
True or false:
If \(I,J \subset {\mathbb{R}}\) are intervals and \(f \colon I \to J\)
is a differentiable bijective (one-to-one and onto) function.
Then \(f^{-1}\) is differentiable.
$BR
END_TEXT
