$PAR
True or false:
If \(I,J \subset {\mathbb{R}}\) are intervals and \(f \colon I \to J\)
is a differentiable surjective (onto) function such that \(f'(x) $GTS 0\)
for every \(x \in I .\)
Then \(f^{-1}\) exists and is differentiable.
$BR
END_TEXT
